item.title: See D.R.A.M. Put A Classical Spin On 'Broccoli'
item.description:
See D.R.A.M. Put A Classical Spin On 'Broccoli'

If you turned on the radio at least once in 2016, you probably heard "Broccoli," D.R.A.M. 's chirpy, carefree collaboration with Lil Yachty. The song went double platinum, topped the Billboard charts, and is even up for a Grammy Award this month, but that doesn't mean D.R.A.M.'s afraid to revise the formula and put a different spin on his much-loved hit.

item.title: Kim Kardashian West and Children Might Have the Coolest Family Airport Style
item.description:
Kim Kardashian West and Children Might Have the Coolest Family Airport Style

Kim Kardashian West is slowly getting back to her old self, and has been picking up her busy travel schedule where she left off in 2016. She was seen jetting out of Van Nuys airport in Los Angeles yesterday with both of her children in tow.

item.title: WorldStar Hip Hop founder Lee 'Q' O'Denat has passed away
item.description:
WorldStar Hip Hop founder Lee 'Q' O'Denat has passed away

Founder of WorldStar Hip Hop Lee "Q" O'Denat passed away in his sleep Monday night at the age of 43, according to TMZ. WorldStar was founded in 2005 primarily as a space to host mixtapes, but quickly developed into an explosive hub of viral videos - ultimately shaping internet culture and launching countless artists into the mainstream, including Mick Jenkins, Migos, Gucci Mane and Wiz Khalifa.

item.title: Lifetime's Michael Jackson Movie Has Found Its King Of Pop
item.description:
Lifetime's Michael Jackson Movie Has Found Its King Of Pop

Michael Jackson biopics are all over the news these days, and unfortunately not in a positive way. There was a huge amount of controversy around a grotesque portrayal of the King of Pop by white actor Joseph Fiennes in the Sky Arts anthology series, Urban Myths, that was pulled due to the Jackson family's outrage.

item.title: Golden Globes 2017: The Best Moments You Didn't See on TV
item.description:
Golden Globes 2017: The Best Moments You Didn't See on TV

On Golden Globes night, the ballroom at the Beverly Hilton has the mood of a raucous, alcohol-permitting high-school cafeteria, where everyone just happens to be wearing couture and hoping to sit at Meryl Streep's table.
